(20, 1, '2010-06-20 21:20:37', '2010-06-20 21:20:37', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The BratMUN conference will take place in the building of National Council of Slovak Republic - simply said, the Slovak parliament. The committees will have pleasant conditions to work in, and a top-notch conference hall for the meetings of General assembly.<a href="../wp-content/uploads/2010/06/nrsr.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-116" style="margin-left: 15px; float: right;" title="National Council of Slovak Republic - image credit http://geocaching.cz" src="../wp-content/uploads/2010/06/nrsr.jpg" alt="National Council of Slovak Republic - a photograph; image credit http://geocaching.cz" width="250" height="188" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>The building </em>of the National Council is situated on an exclusive place in the city. Next to the Bratislava Castle, it offers perfect view of the river Danube, the city, surrounding countries Austria and Hungary, giving you a feeling of perfectly interconnected Europe.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>Transport </em>to the venue is very simple. There are two trolleybus lines, 203 and 207, that operate the stop "Hrad" (Slovak for "Castle"), which is very close to the building, and they leave from the downtown approximately every 10 to 15 minutes. The line 207 also serves the passengers on the stop "Prievozská", the one near the hotel where students from the rest of Slovakia and Europe will be accommodated, You can also make use of one of the numerous taxi services.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="" /></p>', 'The venue', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-venue', '', '', '2010-07-08 23:06:25', '2010-07-08 21:06:25', '', 18, 'http://bratmun.loc/the-conference/the-venue', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(23, 1, '2010-06-20 21:21:17', '2010-06-20 21:21:17', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The BratMUN conference, much like other MUNs, is a  simulation of a real <a href="../wp-content/uploads/2010/06/conference1.png"><img class="alignright" style="margin: 15px 0pt 15px 15px; float: right;" title="At the General Assembly" src="../wp-content/uploads/2010/06/conference1-200x300.png" alt="At the General Assembly" width="200" height="300" /></a>United Nations conference, and so it also proceeds in the same spirit. The conference starts with the opening  ceremony, continues with debates in a number of committees and ends with  a discussion in the General Assembly.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The delegates are required to make research on their countries'' standpoint on issuess discussed in the committees, as th<img alt="" />ey  will be representing their interests. They should have a good insight  into the topics being discussed, so they can provide valuable opinions  and do their best for the country they are representing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">After  the discussion in General Assembly, a resolution is issued. The  resolution should be a consensus of the partaking countries on the  topics discussed. After making a resolutions, it is decided whether it  will be accepted or not by voting.</p>', 'What''s MUN?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'whats-mun', '', '', '2010-07-08 23:13:31', '2010-07-08 21:13:31', '', 18, 'http://bratmun.loc/?page_id=23', 0, 'page', '', 0),
