(25, 1, '2010-06-20 21:22:07', '2010-06-20 21:22:07', 'Bratislava is the capital city of Slovak Republic, with its history spanning to 10th century. It is located on the river Danube, nearby the borders with Austria, Hungary and Czech Republic. It is surrounded by a mountain range <em>Malé Karpaty</em>, with the highest point at 768 meters. The density of population is around 500,000 , making up around 10 percent of the population of Slovakia.\r\n\r\n[gallery link="file"]', 'Geography', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'geography', '', '', '2010-08-26 15:59:10', '2010-08-26 13:59:10', '', 9, 'http://bratmun.loc/?page_id=25', 0, 'page', '', 0),
