(82, 1, '2010-08-04 16:05:03', '2010-08-04 14:05:03', '<h2><span style="font-weight: normal;">Traveling to Bratislava</span></h2>\r\nThe possibilities of getting to Bratislava include almost all common means of transportation. All stations and airports are highlighted on a map below.\r\n\r\n<strong>Traveling by plane</strong>\r\nThere are two airports you can fly to when traveling to Bratislava, the Bratislava airport (<em>BTS</em>) and the Vienna airport - Schwechat (<em>VIE</em>).\r\nThe airport in Bratislava is situated just outside the city itself and is connected with the public transportation system in Bratislava by two bus lines.  (see <em>Traveling around Bratislava</em>)\r\nSchwechat is located in Austria, around 70 km far from the center of Bratislava. When flying to Schwechat, you can get to Bratislava by a bus  (consult <a href="http://www.slovaklines.sk/important-information.html" target="_blank">http://www.slovaklines.sk/important-information.html</a> for further information) that departs from Schwechat every 30 minutes. The journey takes approximately one hour.\r\nLow-cost airlines flying to either Schwechat or Bratislava include Ryanair (BTS), Air Berlin (VIE) and Easy Jet (VIE).\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.airportbratislava.sk/index.aspx?lang=1033" target="_blank">Website of Bratislava airport </a>| <a href="http://www.viennaairport.com/jart/prj3/va/main.jart?rel=en&amp;reserve-mode=active&amp;content-id=1249344074214" target="_blank">Website of Schwechat airport </a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Traveling by train</strong>\r\nWhen traveling by train,  be sure to book your ticket to and arrive at Bratislava - Hlavna Stanica (Main Railway Station), which is situated in the city center, easily accessible by various buses, trolleybuses and trams.\r\nShould you happen to arrive at Bratislava - Petržalka, have no worries, there are more than enough bus lines that will easily take you to the center. (see <em>Traveling around Bratislava</em>)\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.zssk.sk/en" target="_blank">Website of Slovak Rail</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Traveling by bus</strong>\r\nYou can without any problems travel to Bratislava by bus or coach as well. The station you will arrive at when traveling by bus is Bratislava - Mlynské Nivy.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.slovaklines.sk/index_en.html">Website of Slovak Lines</a>\r\n<h2>Traveling around Bratislava</h2>\r\n<strong>Public transport</strong>\r\nThe public transportation system in Bratislava comprises a complex system of bus, trolleybus and tram lines. The whole city is divided into three zones, but the fares vary with different zones only when buying prepaid travel passes (1 month, 3 months or 1 year). The public transport tend to be fairly regular and, especially in the city center, go rather often (some lines even as often as every 5 minutes). The basic rule of thumb applied here is as following: The closer to the city center, the more often the buses go.\r\nFares range from € 0.50 for one-ride 15-minutes ticket and € 0.70 for 60-minutes ticket to € 8.00 for 3-days pass and € 12.00 for a one-week pass. These tickets can be bought in every newspaper agent or in ticket machines (yellow boxes of around 1.2 m in height) which are located by lots of bus and tram stops.\r\nThe complete map of Bratislava public transport can be found in the gallery on the bottom of this page.\r\nSee<a href="http://imhd.zoznam.sk/ba/?w=2e25212e36212c28&amp;lang=en" target="_blank"> iMHD.sk</a> for further information on schedules, lines and fares.\r\n\r\n<strong>Taking a taxi</strong>\r\nThere is a wide range of various taxi services in Bratislava that can be taken either directly on the street or by calling the taxi service via the phone. There will always several taxis standing outside the airport, railway stations or the bus station. What may be strange, though, is the fact that you will be charged more for taking the taxi directly on the street than by calling it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Remember that there will always be a delegation guide assigned to you or your delegation whose responsibility will be to get you on time wherever you need to be (i.e. the hotel or the venue of the conference). Following information are here only should some unforeseen event occur when the delegation guide will not be around.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Getting to the hotel</strong>\r\nThe nearest bus stop to the hotel is the stop called <em>Miletičova. </em>Buses and trolleybuses stopping at this stop are as follows: 70 (bus), 201, 202, 207, 208 (trolleybuses) and N72 (night bus).\r\n\r\nIf coming from the airport, take the bus number 61 down to the citym get out of the bus at <em>Trnavské Mýto, </em>go across the road and take the trolleybus 201, direction <em>Čilížska. </em>\r\n\r\nIf coming from the main railway station, take the trolleybus 201, direction <em>Čilížska.</em>\r\n\r\nIf coming from the Petržalka railway station, take the bus number 91, direction <em>Nový Most</em>, get out at the last stop, <em>Nový Most</em>, and take the bus 70, direction <em>ŽST Podunajské Biskupice.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Getting to the venue of the conference</strong>\r\nThe venue of the conference, the National Council of the Slovak Republic, is located next to Bratislava Castle on the hill above the city (see <em>Venue</em>). The bus stop that is closest to the National Council is called <em>Hrad</em>, at which trolleybuses 203 and 207 stop.\r\n\r\nIf going from the hotel, take the trolleybus number 207, direction <em>Valašská.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Getting to the city center</strong>\r\nWhen coming from the National Council, take either 203 or 207, direction <em>Koliba </em>and <em>Ružová Dolina </em>respectively, and get out at stops <em>Hodžovo námestie </em>or <em>Námestie Slobody</em>, which are basically in the city center. See the <em>Where to eat </em>section for tips on restaurants, pubs and bars in the city center.\r\n\r\nWhen coming from the hotel, you can take the 207, direction <em>Valašská</em>, and get down at <em>Hodžovo námestie </em>or <em>Námestie Slobody. </em>You can also take 208, direction <em>Šulekova</em>, and get out of the bus at <em>Kollárovo námestie </em>or <em>Hodžovo námestie</em>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Maps</strong>\r\n\r\n[gallery link="file"]', 'Transportation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-autosave', '', '', '2010-08-04 16:05:03', '2010-08-04 14:05:03', '', 28, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
