(115, 1, '2010-07-08 23:07:26', '2010-07-08 21:07:26', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The BratMUN conference will take place in the building of National Council of Slovak Republic - simply said, the Slovak parliament. The committees will have pleasant conditions to work in, and a top-notch conference hall for the meetings of General assembly.<a href="../wp-content/uploads/2010/06/nrsr.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-116" style="margin-left: 15px; float: right;" title="National Council of Slovak Republic - image credit http://geocaching.cz" src="../wp-content/uploads/2010/06/nrsr.jpg" alt="National Council of Slovak Republic - a photograph; image credit http://geocaching.cz" width="250" height="188" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>The building </em>of the National Council is situated on an exclusive place in the city. Next to the Bratislava Castle, it offers perfect view of the river Danube, the city, surrounding countries Austria and Hungary, giving you a feeling of perfectly interconnected Europe.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>Transport </em>to the venue is very simple. There are two trolleybus lines, 203 and 207, that operate the stop "Hrad" (Slovak for "Castle"), which is very close to the building, and they leave from the downtown approximately every 10 to 15 minutes. The line 207 also serves the passengers on the stop "Prievozská", the one near the hotel where students from the rest of Slovakia and Europe will be accommodated, You can also make use of one of the numerous taxi services.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="" /></p>', 'The venue', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-autosave', '', '', '2010-07-08 23:07:26', '2010-07-08 21:07:26', '', 20, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
