(180, 1, '2010-08-16 17:24:03', '2010-08-16 15:24:03', '<h2>North Korea</h2>\r\n<strong><a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Security_Council.pdf">Download the study guide</a></strong>\r\n\r\n\r\nOn 26 March 2010, South Korean naval ship has been sunk by the borders of the North Korea. Today, South Korea claims to have proof that verifies that the torpedo sinking this ship has been fired by the northern neighbor, North Korea, which denies the guilt. The response to accusations was serious, North Korea severed all bonds with South Korea, forbidding any South Korean ship or plane to be present on their territory.\r\n\r\nThis restriction goes straight against the Resolution 1874 adopted by United Nations, which encourages the inspection and seizure of cargo suspected of being connected to nuclear weapons development because of North Korea''s refusal of disarmament. On top of that, the situation is becoming acute, as can be seen from reactions of both parties in this conflict and the significantly powerful and important former ally of North Korea, China. China claims to make reasonable decision about the situation - on which side to stand - on its own, not willing to disrupt peace, but not stating the side which they would stand by in case of an open conflict. Therefore they are not explicitly denying the possibility of sticking with North Korea. Hence, it is not unlikely that an armed conflict will break out and as the UN is not able to monitor the arsenal situation in North Korea, when taken to further extent, the possibility of second Korean War such as the conflict in 50''s may be relevant, affecting the lives of millions.\r\n\r\nHence the reason why UN SC should intervene. The question is how. Should they lift the sanctions, tighten them up or leave the sanctions as they are? Or should the UN solve this problem in a different way?\r\n\r\n<strong>Jakub Páleník</strong>\r\n', 'Security Council', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'security-council', '', '', '2010-09-26 22:41:12', '2010-09-26 20:41:12', '', 49, 'http://bratmun.sk/?page_id=180', 0, 'page', '', 0),
