(264, 1, '2010-08-16 17:12:51', '2010-08-16 15:12:51', 'Following documents ought to be read by all delegates prior to attending the conference. They include the most essential document, Rules of Procedure, as well as documents which will help you find your way around the debate during the MUN and provide you with tips on how to prepare for the committees the best.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Annotated+Rules+of+Procedure+2006.doc"><strong>Rules of Procedure</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Policy+statement.doc">How to write a policy statement</a>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/FlowofDebateChart.pdf">Flow of the debate (a chart)</a>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/termsphrases.doc">Essential terms and phrases</a>', 'MUN Rules', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '38-revision-4', '', '', '2010-08-16 17:12:51', '2010-08-16 15:12:51', '', 38, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(274, 1, '2010-10-18 10:02:02', '2010-10-18 08:02:02', '<h2>Global Warming</h2>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/StudyGuide_SCC.pdf"><strong>Download the Study Guide</strong></a>\r\n\r\nGlobal warming is nowadays one of the most debated worldwide issues. It’s a huge problem that affects countries round the world. These countries must make important decisions in order to stop global warming. Past attempts to tackle the problem at Kyoto and in Copenhagen have failed; because resolutions were not supported by all key states involved in this issue and not adequate to mitigate global warming. Therefore the delegates from the countries affected by this issue will meet at BratMUN in a UN Summit on Climate Change. They ought to discuss this topic and find new solutions, which will be supported by all of them.\r\n\r\nWe have to make a new worldwide treaty which will bring effective solutions for adaptation and mitigation of global warming. It should replace all previous treaties and ought to be accepted by all involved countries. Our main aims are devising ways to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, finding ways to deploy climate-friendly technology, and financing adaptation and mitigation measures. We have to make a proposal adequate for all countries that can influence this present and pressing problem. It’s the right time to make big decisions, which can bring us positive results. Our future is in our hands.\r\n\r\n<strong>Dominika Belešová</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>', 'Summit on Climate Change', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '194-autosave', '', '', '2010-10-18 10:02:02', '2010-10-18 08:02:02', '', 194, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(275, 1, '2010-09-03 22:38:53', '2010-09-03 20:38:53', '<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #333399;">BratMUN 2010</span></strong></h1>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Bratislava Model United Nations</strong></h3>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>5th - 7th November 2010</strong></h2>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Welcome to the BratMUN website!</h2>\r\nWe are looking forward to seeing you at our conference in November. Should you have any question regarding BratMUN, please do not hesitate to contact us.\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">BratMUN team</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Please bear in mind the registration deadline, the <span style="color: #ff0000;">10th of October</span>. You can register online </strong><a href="http://bratmun.sk/registration/registration-form"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></h2>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-11', '', '', '2010-09-03 22:38:53', '2010-09-03 20:38:53', '', 7, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(276, 1, '2010-08-31 17:51:09', '2010-08-31 15:51:09', '<h2><strong>DATES</strong></h2>\r\nConference: <strong>5th to 7th November 2010</strong>\r\nRegister until: <strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">10th October 2010</span></strong>\r\n<h2><strong>FEES</strong></h2>\r\nDelegates from Bratislava: <strong>35€</strong>\r\nDelegates from Slovakia: <strong>65€</strong>\r\nDelegates from abroad: <strong>105€</strong>\r\n\r\nRegistration fee includes three nights accommodation with breakfast and lunch during the conference, plus dinner at the banquet. Transportation to Bratislava is<strong> not included</strong> in the registration fee.\r\nAll delegations from one school must have a teacher - faculty advisor accompanying them. The tfaculty advisor will need to be registered as well, but <strong>won’t</strong> be paying any fee.', 'Dates and fees', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-13', '', '', '2010-08-31 17:51:09', '2010-08-31 15:51:09', '', 32, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(277, 1, '2010-08-16 17:27:47', '2010-08-16 15:27:47', '<h2>Greece</h2>\r\nDear delegates,\r\n\r\nIt is our pleasure to welcome you in the EU committee. This year, we are dealing with a major financial crisis which has occurred in Greece. Over the past years, Greek government was systematically spending significantly more money than they collected in tax revenues. This set of policies brought the country to an edge of bankruptcy. Although during the 2000s Greek economy was one of the fastest growing in Europe, at present time it has the second highest government deficit in the world, which was estimated to be 13.6% of GDP. The large deficit does not endanger only the local economy, but has international implications as well. A number of European banks purchased government bonds that now cannot be paid back, a fall in volume of trade in south east Europe puts the neighboring states in trouble, and, most importantly, the basic currency – Euro is losing its value due to the instability.\r\n\r\nTherefore, an immediate intervention has to be made. Delegates belonging to the EU committee will be negotiating a solution to the Greek debt crisis in two phases. The first one, taking place in late April of 2010 will consist of presentation of the attitudes, conditions and possible solutions of the delegates regarding the crisis after Greece officially asked the EU for financial help. The aim of the second session on May 2, 2010 will be the actual ratification of the loan to Greece.\r\n\r\nWe hope to see you in one of the most dramatic Committees of this year’s BratMUN!\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\n<strong>Andrea Schmidtová and Lucia Tibenská</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Download the Study Guide</strong>', 'World Bank', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '187-revision-2', '', '', '2010-08-16 17:27:47', '2010-08-16 15:27:47', '', 187, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
