(290, 1, '2010-09-19 16:37:27', '2010-09-19 14:37:27', '<h2><span style="color: #000000;">The worldwide issue of extremism</span></h2>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/StudyGuide_Extremism.pdf"><strong>Download the Study Guide</strong></a>\r\n\r\nWe hear the word “extremism” almost on daily basis from the news in connection with various topics, however without a proper explanation of what it actually is. Nowadays, connections like Islamic extremists or radicals are made quite often, with only knowledge, that it is something bad, perhaps morally incorrect. It is however important to realize the whole concept of extremism.\r\nStarting by looking on the root of this word, “extreme”, points to the fact, that it is something beyond the regular limits of acceptance. Types of extremism vary, but we are able to create a general definition.\r\nExtremism has different ways of being expressed, ranging from verbal, through graphic, to physical activities. These are based on ideological views of certain groups of individuals whose ideas and opinions significantly differ from the ones generally accepted by the society, often containing signs of violence and intolerance towards certain religions, races, sexual orientation, look and many more factors.\r\nIndividuals having extremist views often express their dislike, or rather intolerance to aforementioned factors through fight against health, life, physical property, any democratic principles or order in law, hoping that once the order is disturbed, they would be able to enforce their ideologies. Extremists are not willing to accept the law and any ethical/moral principles when pursuing their visions and the most serious problem is the aggression used as tool to enforce these principles.\r\nThere are several extremist organizations; however two main groups can be distinguished; left and right oriented extremists.\r\nRight oriented groups include Hooligans who ignite the violence amongst the sport spectators, Neo-Nazis and Skinheads often suppressing rights of certain minorities, racial extremists spreading racial hate and others. Such groups acquire and maintain their “popularity” amongst specific individuals through violent/aggressive activities and abusive behavior.\r\nLeft oriented extremists include radical anarchy groups, ecological and environmental extremists, radical anti-fascism and anti-Nazism groups but also extremist skateboarding and graffiti groups. All of these have common features of damaging properties, abusing human rights and health as well as disrespecting the law.\r\n\r\nThe basic common signs of any extremist group, besides those already mentioned earlier, are: a leader with usually strong rhetorical skills used to gain control over the individuals inside the group and to affect their perception and reasoning, unity amongst members with common disrespect for the other, non extremist, individuals, any group specific rules all members must oblige, and very commonly used psychological manipulation, especially when recruiting new members, also called “love bombing”.\r\nIt is a paradox that within such arrogant and violent groups occurs an activity with such name; however its purpose has nothing to do with love whatsoever. Love bombing is a term used to describe the act of deliberate show of friendship by a group of people towards other individuals motivated by desire to somehow influence these individuals and subliminally force them to do, what the “love bombers” or in other words the extremist groups, wants them to do.\r\nShall we return now to the example mentioned in the beginning, the example of Islamic extremists, we see now, that they are individuals disrespecting morally/ethically correct behavior, trying to enforce their ideologies through aggression and blindly following particular leaders, who control them through, we may say, extremist sort of propaganda.\r\nOn the other hand, it is important to differentiate between extremists and innocent people, and avoid hasty generalizations and stereotyping. Extremist groups may be found anywhere and their ideologies are based on many different factors, hence one shall be careful when putting extremism and a group of people together, as not all Muslims or Arabs are extremists, as well as not all bald people are necessarily skinheads etc.\r\nExtremism is one of the factors influencing today’s world state of potential peace and carries devastating problems for the countries. It affects economy, welfare and life of the people. Sadly, the death toll caused by extremist groups is rising and a huge number of victims are innocent civilians. It is a very serious problem, and should be treated with caution, however strictly.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ahmed Abadl</strong>', 'Human Rights Committee', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'human-rights-committee', '', '', '2010-11-03 20:55:21', '2010-11-03 19:55:21', '', 49, 'http://bratmun.sk/?page_id=290', 8, 'page', '', 0),
