(325, 1, '2010-09-21 20:12:42', '2010-09-21 18:12:42', 'Following documents ought to be read by all delegates prior to attending the conference. They include the most essential document, Rules of Procedure, as well as documents which will help you find your way around the debate during the MUN and provide you with tips on how to prepare for the committees the best.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/rules_of_procedure_for_delegates.pdf"><strong>Rules of Procedure</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/How_to_write_a_policy_statement.pdf">How to write a policy statement</a>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Path_to_a_draft_resolution.pdf">Path to a draft resolution</a>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Flow_of_the_debate.pdf">Flow of the debate (a chart)</a>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/terms_and_phrases.pdf">Essential terms and phrases</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/country_matrix1.pdf">Country matrix</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Conference_schedule.pdf">Conference schedule</a>', 'MUN Rules', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '38-revision-13', '', '', '2010-09-21 20:12:42', '2010-09-21 18:12:42', '', 38, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(326, 1, '2010-10-02 16:57:57', '2010-10-02 14:57:57', '', 'EU_Study_Guide', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'eu_study_guide', '', '', '2010-10-02 16:57:57', '2010-10-02 14:57:57', '', 0, 'http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/EU_Study_Guide.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(327, 1, '2010-10-02 16:59:12', '2010-10-02 14:59:12', '<h2>Greece</h2>\r\n<a href="http://bratmun.sk/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/EU_Study_Guide.pdf"><strong>Download the Study Guide</strong></a>\r\n\r\nDear delegates,\r\n\r\nIt is our pleasure to welcome you in the EU committee. This year, we are dealing with a major financial crisis which has occurred in Greece. Over the past years, Greek government was systematically spending significantly more money than they collected in tax revenues. This set of policies brought the country to an edge of bankruptcy. Although during the 2000s Greek economy was one of the fastest growing in Europe, at present time it has the second highest government deficit in the world, which was estimated to be 13.6% of GDP. The large deficit does not endanger only the local economy, but has international implications as well. A number of European banks purchased government bonds that now cannot be paid back, a fall in volume of trade in south east Europe puts the neighboring states in trouble, and, most importantly, the basic currency – Euro is losing its value due to the instability.\r\n\r\nTherefore, an immediate intervention has to be made. Delegates belonging to the EU committee will be negotiating a solution to the Greek debt crisis in two phases. The first one, taking place in late April of 2010 will consist of presentation of the attitudes, conditions and possible solutions of the delegates regarding the crisis after Greece officially asked the EU for financial help. The aim of the second session on May 2, 2010 will be the actual ratification of the loan to Greece.\r\n\r\nWe hope to see you in one of the most dramatic Committees of this year’s BratMUN!\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\n<strong>Andrea Schmidtová and Lucia Tibenská</strong>', 'European Union', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '187-autosave', '', '', '2010-10-02 16:59:12', '2010-10-02 14:59:12', '', 187, 'http://bratmun.sk/%page%', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
