(6, '<h2 style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Official BratMUN 2011 Contact &amp; Delegation Services Contact</strong><br />\r\n	e-mail:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:bratmun@bratmun.sk">bratmun@bratmun.sk</a><br />\r\n	web:&nbsp;<a href="http://bratmun.sk">www.bratmun.sk</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><strong>Main Managers</strong><br />\r\n	Dominik Hatiar<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:dhatiar@hotmail.com">dhatiar@hotmail.com</a><br />\r\n	tel: + 421 949 818 377</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Tomas Mjartan<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:tomas.mjartan@me.com">tomas.mjartan@me.com</a><br />\r\n	tel: + 421 910 230 177</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<strong>Project Supervisor</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">PhDr. Eva Žitn&aacute;<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:zitna@gjh.sk">zitna@gjh.sk</a><br />\r\n	tel: +421 2 5557 11 22</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><strong>Organizing School</strong><br />\r\n	Gymn&aacute;zium Jura Hronca<br />\r\n	Novohradsk&aacute; 3<br />\r\n	821 09 Bratislava<br />\r\n	Slovakia</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><strong>Bank Account Information</strong><br />\r\n	Nad&aacute;cia Novohradsk&aacute;<br />\r\n	account number: 11469293/0900<br />\r\n	&nbsp;administrated by: Slovensk&aacute; sporiteľňa, a.s. Bratislava<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:nadacia@gjh.sk">nadacia@gjh.sk</a></span></p>\r\n', 'about_contact'),
(5, '<h2 style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="georgia, serif">The Organization Team</font></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><strong>Main Managers</strong><br />\r\n	Dominik Hatiar<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:dhatiar@hotmail.com">dhatiar@hotmail.com</a><br />\r\n	tel: + 421 949 818 377</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Tom&aacute;&scaron; Mjartan<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:tomas.mjartan@me.com">tomas.mjartan@me.com</a><br />\r\n	tel: + 421 910 230 177</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><strong>Project Supervisor</strong><br />\r\n	PhDr. Eva Žitn&aacute;<br />\r\n	e-mail: <a href="mailto:zitna@gjh.sk">zitna@gjh.sk</a><br />\r\n	tel: +421 2 5557 11 22</span></p>\r\n', 'about_our_team'),
(4, '<h1>\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">What is BratMUN ?</span></h1>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Most fundamentally, BratMUN is a simulation of the United Nations General Assembly. However, due to the various constraints a Model UN faces, only certain parts of the UN General Assembly are simulated. The Conference is administrated according to the Rules, which are in parallel with the UN rules of procedure. Each school attending the Conference represents one or more Member Nations and each Member Nation is represented by a delegation of two or more delegates. The main goals of the simulation are:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	Click here to download further documents about BratMUN</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Education in the field of international relations and diplomacy;</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Acquainting yourselves with the functioning and the role of the UN in the world;</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Getting to know other cultures and nations, their views on various global issues, and why they have these views and opinions;</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Improving your rhetoric and negotiating skills;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'what_is_bratmunn'),
(1, '<p>\r\n	This is about us</p>\r\n', 'about_main'),
(2, '<h1>\r\n	Invitation letters</h1>\r\n<h1>\r\n	&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><span style="font-size:14px;">If your delegation needs invitation letters, please contact us after registering at bratmun@bratmun.sk and our team will help you.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'bratmun2011_invitation_letters'),
(7, '<p class="Heading10" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:13.55pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:11.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;\r\nbackground:transparent">\r\n	<img alt="BratMUN 2010" src="http://img710.imageshack.us/img710/9347/conference.jpg" style="width: 930px; height: 132px; " /></p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	<b>What is MUN?</b></p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	The BratMUN conference, much like other MUNs that are held all over the world, is a simulation of a real United Nations conference, which means it also proceeds in the same spirit. The conference starts with an opening ceremony, continues with debates in a number of committees and ends with a discussion in the General Assembly.</p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	High school students have an opportunity of acting as ambassadors and delegates at the UN (Security Council, General Assembly or its committees), where they discuss current global political, social, economic, or military issues.</p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	The delegates are required to do research into their countries&#39; standpoint on the issues discussed in the committees, as they will be representing their interests. They should have a good insight into the topics being discussed, so as to provide valuable opinions and to do their best for the country they are representing.</p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	After the discussion in General Assembly, a resolution is issued. The resolution should be a consensus of the partaking countries on the topics discussed. Having agreed on resolutions, it will be decided whether they are accepted or not by voting.</p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	BratMUN is focused on education of students in the area of international relations and diplomacy. The delegates develop important skills, such as critical thinking, negotiation, compromise-making and public speaking.</p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:11.8pt;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;line-height:13.9pt;background:transparent">\r\n	Furthermore, they are inspired and motivated by presence of politicians and ambassadors, who attend the opening ceremony to give their speeches (politicians from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Slovak Republic, Slovak or foreign ambassadors in Slovakia).</p>\r\n<p class="BodyText1" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:.25in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:1.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:14.15pt;\r\nbackground:transparent">\r\n	By meeting all of these challenges, students develop self-confidence and self-esteem. They gain better overview of the political and international affairs of this world.</p>\r\n', 'about_what_is_bratmun'),
(8, '<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><b>Main Sponsors:</b></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Visegrad Fund</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Nad&aacute;cia Slovenskej sporiteľne</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<b>Sponsors:</b></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	UNIS Vienna</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Coca-Cola</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	British Council</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<b>Parters:</b></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Slovak Republic</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	National Council of the Slovak Republic</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	Nad&aacute;cia Novohradsk&aacute;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	BKIS</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	J&amp;T Real Estate</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'about_sponsoring'),
(21, '<p>\r\n	<b>Study Guides</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNGA </b>(General Assembly)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: David Dutko</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Future of the New Arab Democracies</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/GA%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>DISEC </b>(Committee on Disarmament and Security)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Mai Nguyen Phuc</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: The Convention on Cluster Munitions</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/DISEC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>ECOFIN </b>(Economical and Financial Committee)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: D&aacute;vid Žitňansk&yacute; &amp; Trung Dang Quoc</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Future of the USD as the Global Reserve Currency</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/ECOFIN%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNHRC </b>(Human Rights Committee)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Branislav Skoček</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: The Syrian Revolution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/UNHRC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>SPECPOL </b>(Special Political and Decolonization Committee)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Zuzana Vančov&aacute;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Cyprus Dispute</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/SPECPOL%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNODC </b>(United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Alexandra Lačokov&aacute;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Afghani Opium Trade</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/UNODC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNSC </b>(United Nations Security Council)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Richard Svoc&aacute;k</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: South Kordofan Conflict</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/UNSC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Visegrad 4 Committee</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Sabine Hoferov&aacute;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: A Common Energy Policy &amp; V4 Foreign Relations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/V4%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n', 'preparation_study_guide'),
(10, '<h2 style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<b><span style="font-family: georgia, serif; ">Welcome to Bratislava Model United Nations 2011 Conference!</span></b></h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<strong>Further information &nbsp;</strong><em>(25 October, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dear Delegates,</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are only ten days (240 hours) left until the opening ceremony of BratMUN 2011, and consequently it is our duty to provide you with several key pieces of <span id="roll" style="text-decoration: underline; ">information</span>.&nbsp;<u><span id="seeless">See less</span></u></p>\r\n<div id="more_info">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<strong>Study Guides </strong><em>(17 October, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	We are pleased to announce that all &nbsp;study guides have been published. Download them at the &#39;Committees&#39; section of the website.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<strong>General Assembly Study Guide&nbsp;</strong><em>(13 October, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	The General Assembly and UNSC Study Guides have been&nbsp;<a href="http://bratmun.sk/page.php?id=preparation_study_guide" target="_blank">published</a>. More following soon.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<strong>Study Guides&nbsp;</strong><em>(10 October, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	The first four Study Guides just have been&nbsp;<a href="http://bratmun.sk/page.php?id=preparation_study_guide" target="_blank">published</a>. More following soon.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<strong>Registration closed!&nbsp;</strong><em>(4 October, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	The registration has been officially announced closed, as the capacity has been filled completely. We would like to express our gratitude to all the delegations registered.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	We will be sending all the delegations their countries assigned tomorrow (5 Oct), and publishing Study Guides shortly.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	The BratMUN Team is looking forward to meeting you all in November.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<strong>A slight change in the conference fees! </strong><em>(10 September, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	Please visit our <a href="http://bratmun.sk/page.php?id=bratmun2011_conference_fees">conference fees site</a>! The check in and check out exact times have also been released at the <a href="http://bratmun.sk/page.php?id=bratmun2011_conference_schedule">conference schedule site</a>!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Registration has opened!</b> <i>(5 September, 2011)</i></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The registration for Bratislava Model United Nations 2011 Conference has been opened. We have also revealed the <a href="http://www.bratmun.sk/page.php?id=committess_main">committee topics</a>, participation fees, travel information and published a unique preparation document for delegates - &quot;<a href="http://www.bratmun.sk/page.php?id=preparation_mun_rules">BratMUN: The Complete Guide</a>&quot;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Moreover, a few days ago BratMUN has become one of the world&#39;s first MUNs and youth conferences to have its own promo video. Get a preview of the atmosphere of the conference and the Bratislava city by watching the epic video <a href="http://www.bratmun.sk/page.php?id=video">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The BratMUN team is looking forward to meeting you all in November!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><strong>Foreword In</strong></span><strong>vitation</strong><em> (28 July, 2011)</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	<span style="color:#ffffff;">Read the foreword invitation to the BratMUN 2011 conference by one of the main managers of the project </span><a href="http://www.bratmun.sk/page.php?id=none_invitation"><span style="color:#ffffff;">here</span></a><span style="color:#ffffff;">.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia, serif; "><b>Registration Opening Date Announced&nbsp;</b><em>(13 July, 2011)</em></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="georgia, serif">The registration of the BratMUN 2011 Conference is going to open on September 5th. We will be bringing you more news throughout the summer. The BratMUN promo video is going to premiere on August 20th alongside with the committee topics shortly afterwards. In case of any questions, do not hesitate to contact us at bratmun@bratmun.sk</font></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-family: georgia, serif; "><b>Dates of the Conference Announced!</b>&nbsp;<em>(</em></span><span style="font-family: georgia, serif; "><em>28</em></span> <span style="font-family: georgia, serif; "><em>May, 2011)</em></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="georgia, serif">The BratMUN Organization Team is pleased to officially announce the dates of the eleventh Bratislava Model United Nations Conference. BratMUN 2011 is going to take place on November 4, 5, and 6 in the venues of the National Council of the Slovak Republic.&nbsp;</font></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b><span style="font-family: georgia, serif; ">BratMUN 2011 Under Auspices of Ministry of foreign affairs of the Slovak Republic&nbsp;</span></b><span style="font-family: georgia, serif; "><em>(19 April, 2011)</em></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are very delighted to announce that as of April 19th 2011, the BratMUN 2011 Conference is supported by Ministry of foreign affairs of the Slovak republic. The Organization Team is looking forward to cooperation with this institution, as it has been exceedingly successful in the last couple of years of the BratMUN conference.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<div>\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'index'),
(11, '<center>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<a href="http://facebook.com/bratmun" target="_blank"><img src="http://public.bloog.us/facebook.png" /></a> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href="http://twitter.com/bratmun" target="_blank"><img src="http://public.bloog.us/twitter-2.png" /></a> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href="http://foursquare.com/bratmun" target="_blank"><img src="http://public.bloog.us/foursquare.png" /></a> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href="http://youtube.com/bratmun2011" target="_blank"><img src="http://public.bloog.us/youtube.png" /></a><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</center>\r\n', 'about_social_net'),
(26, '<p>\r\n	<b>BratMUN History</b></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	It was 11 years after the Velvet Revolution, an uprising organized by students began in the former Czechoslovakia, resulting in the final end of the communist rule. November 1989 is a very significant date to all Czechs and Slovaks who took part in the massive demonstrations against the radical totalitarian communist regime that oppressed Slovaks for more than 30 years. The fall of communism has given people back their natural freedoms, a functioning democratic system, as well as the opportunity to interact with the international community.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	BratMUN was founded in the year 2000 by a group of IB students studying at the Gymn&aacute;zium Jura Hronca in Bratislava. The establishment of a regular Model United Nations (abbreviated to MUN) conference in Bratislava is also one of the positive consequences of the Velvet revolution. Thus, it is a symbolical duty for the conference to take place in November. BratMUN offers its participants the opportunity to learn about the major global challenges, experience multiculturalism and global diversity, and many other useful aspects that were almost impossible to encounter here 22 years ago.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	At its beginnings, BratMUN was one of a few MUN conferences in Central and Eastern Europe. Today there are many more MUNs, but BratMUN still remains the only MUN in Slovakia, which emphasizes its importance. The quality and size of the conferences has been improving from year to year. The last three sessions have been held in the venue of the National Council of the Slovak Republic, the most dignified venue possible. We, the organizers, are opening the second decade of BratMUN conferences with many improvements and changes that will hopefully satisfy every delegate.</div>\r\n', 'about_history_of_bratmun'),
(13, '<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n	<img alt="Bratislava" src="http://img52.imageshack.us/img52/6338/543677852540d439c540b.jpg" style="width: 930px; height: 389px; " /></p>\r\n<p style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: left; ">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="7"><b><font class="Apple-style-span" size="3"><strong><font size="3">Welcome to Europe&#39;s most glamorous city!</font></strong></font></b></font></p>\r\n<p style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: left; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">Well, all right, not quite. And, truth be told, Bratislava, with fewer than half a million people, is never likely to be Europe&#39;s most glamorous city.&nbsp; But it might be Europe&#39;s most relaxed one, because what this city does is have old-town charm, sophisticated restaurants, traditional pubs, good music ranging from jazz to opera, stylish people, and a humanocentric scale, which means that as a visitor you will not spend half your day trekking in and out of underground stations or getting from the airport into town. &nbsp;All this, and Europe&#39;s greatest river as a backdrop. What more could you want?</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">Known as Pressburg to the speakers of German or Pozsony in Hungarian, Bratislava got its present name only 90 years ago.&nbsp; However, the city has a long and proud history that dates back to pre-Roman times.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">The hillsides on the edge of the city have been home to vineyards for centuries, and close to Bratislava are wine towns where you can taste the best - and it is startlingly good! - that Slovakia has to offer.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">In the city itself there is plenty to see and do. Bratislava&#39;s long history - as a home to Celts, Romans, Germans, Hungarians, Jews, and, of course, Slovaks - means there is an impressive variety of architecture, languages and cuisine.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">The handsome homes of the Austro-Hungarian noble families who built palaces here dot the city, and many of them are now open to the public as museums and galleries.&nbsp; The castle, with its long and chequered history (it has been destroyed more than once), is now undergoing a major restoration.&nbsp; There are great views over the mediaeval old town and the Danube valley from its fortifications.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">Communism too left its mark: across the river, the unmistakable ranks of concrete housing blocks - &quot;panel&aacute;ky&quot; in Slovak - line the horizon, with the unique UFO-style bridge in the foreground.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">The Danube River itself is, of course, one of the city&#39;s main assets.&nbsp; There are numerous cafes along its banks, within walking distance of the centre. The &#39;UFO&#39; itself contains an eponymous bar high above the river. The pedestrian decks of the New and Old Bridges are good places to watch the river traffic, including huge Danube barges, glide past. Alternatively, you can take to the water yourself: daily hydrofoil services link the city with nearby Vienna.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">Big pop acts often play concerts in Bratislava, while the Slovak Philharmonic and the opera and ballet of the Slovak National Theatre regularly put on world-class performances.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">Numerous restaurants offering international cuisine - from Slovak to French to Argentinian to Japanese - and excellent local beer and wine fill the city centre, alongside lively bars, lounges and clubs.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">If, having enjoying the food and drink, you feel like walking - or biking - there are almost unlimited opportunities in the forested hills to the north of the city, or along the Danube to the south, where inline skating is also very popular on the scores of kilometres of traffic-free paths.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><font class="Apple-style-span"><font class="Apple-style-span">And, if, after all this, you still want some big-city &#39;glamour&#39; - and, along it, busloads of gormless tourists - Vienna, Budapest or Prague are close enough for a daytrip.</font></font></span></div>\r\n<div style="padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class="sf" style="float: none !important; display: block; clear: both; font-size: 9px; line-height: 0px; height: 1px; border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: justify; ">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<div style="text-align: justify; ">\r\n		<span style="font-size:14px;">visit.bratislava.sk</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'bratmun2011_bratislava'),
(25, '<p>\r\n	<iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="550" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/Zsl6xenu16c&amp;hl=nl&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;hd=1&amp;autoplay=1" style="z-index: -999;" width="925"></iframe></p>\r\n', 'video'),
(22, '<p>\r\n	<b>Position Papers</b><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px ''Adobe Garamond Pro''">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">Good preparation is a key to any delegations&rsquo; success at the Conference. In order to perform well, you should understand the way the country you represent works and behaves in the international area. With this knowledge you can faithfully defend your country&rsquo;s position on the topics we will be discussing in the committees. In order to be able to propose realistic actions, you will need to understand the basic elements of the UN and its members (your country).</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px ''Adobe Garamond Pro''">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px ''Adobe Garamond Pro''">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">The Chairpersons prepare Study Guides for each Committee so as to provide you with some basic information on our topics and to give you pointers for future research. Please read and discuss the guides among yourselves to get the most out of them, but remember that the guides are here to get you started and that you should also do research on your own. The suggestions for further research included at the end of Study Guides will help you with that. Remember that the Internet is full of sources, but also bear in mind that not all can be equally valuable and useful, therefore be selective but open while doing research.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px ''Adobe Garamond Pro''">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px ''Adobe Garamond Pro''">\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">To help the Chairpersons better prepare the committees for you, they will be asking you all to send them policy statements (1 page, typed) both for the General Assembly topic, and the Committee topics your country will be dealing with.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;">For more information and tips on how to write a policy statement, please refer to article &quot;How to Write a Policy Statement&quot; on pages 27, 28 and 28 of <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/BratMUN%20-%20The%20Complete%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">BratMUN: The Complete Guide</a> publication.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'preparation_position_papers'),
