(9, '<p>\r\n	<b>Accommodation</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are providing accommodation in Hotel Astra*** for the delegates paying the 65&euro; fee. Find out more about the hotel here:&nbsp;http://www.hotelastra.sk/en<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="http://hotelastra.sk/images/hotelmain.jpg" style="width: 254px; height: 169px; " />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://hotelastra.sk/gallery/thumb/apartman1_thumb.jpg" style="width: 252px; height: 169px; " /><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'bratmun2011_hotel_accomodation'),
(18, '<p>\r\n	<img alt="Bratislava Travel" src="http://img153.imageshack.us/img153/8962/bratmunmap.png" style="width: 930px; height: 179px; " /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>DELEGATES ACCOMMODATED AT THE HOTEL NEED TO ARRIVE TO BRATISLAVA BEFORE 9PM, NOVEMBER 3rd </b>(Thursday)<b>&nbsp;<br />\r\n	There are going to be Delegation Guides waiting for each delegation upon their arrival.</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Flights</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are two airports you can use to get comfortably to Bratislava. The city&#39;s own international airport is with it&#39;s brand new terminal rather small, but provides flights to almost all Europe&#39;s major cities and destinations. There is, on the other hand, Vienna Airport which provides connection to hundreds of destinations all over the world just a handful of kilometers from Bratislava. It takes only about 30 minutes by car, or 40 minutes by regular bus lines to get from the Vienna Airport to Bratislava.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.airportbratislava.sk/index.aspx?lang=1033" target="_blank">Website of Bratislava Airport</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.viennaairport.com/jart/prj3/va/main.jart?rel=en&amp;reserve-mode=active&amp;content-id=1249344074214" target="_blank">Website of Vienna Airport</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Bus</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Traveling to Bratislava by a bus is extremely popular nowadays. Bus service connects to numerous locations all across Europe and brings you comfort of Wi-Fi for longer travels.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<a href="http://www.slovaklines.sk/index_en.html" target="_blank">Website of Eurolines Slovakia</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Railways</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://www.zssk.sk/en" target="_blank">Website of Slovak Rails</a>&nbsp;- find your connection to Bratislava from hundreds of destinations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please note that all delegates must arrive to Bratislava on Thursday, November 3rd, since the conference starts on November 4th morning.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'bratmun2011_travel_info'),
(19, '<p>\r\n	<b>Committees</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The following committee topics are offered at this year&#39;s conference.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNGA </b>(General Assembly)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: David Dutko</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Future of the New Arab Democracies</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/GA%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>DISEC </b>(Committee on Disarmament and Security)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Mai Nguyen Phuc</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: The Convention on Cluster Munitions</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/DISEC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>ECOFIN </b>(Economical and Financial Committee)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: D&aacute;vid Žitňansk&yacute; &amp; Trung Dang Quoc</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Future of the USD as the Global Reserve Currency</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/ECOFIN%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNHRC </b>(Human Rights Committee)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Branislav Skoček</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: The Syrian Revolution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/UNHRC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>SPECPOL </b>(Special Political and Decolonization Committee)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Zuzana Vančov&aacute;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Cyprus Dispute</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/SPECPOL%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNODC </b>(United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Alexandra Lačokov&aacute;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: Afghani Opium Trade</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/UNODC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>UNSC </b>(United Nations Security Council)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Richard Svoc&aacute;k</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: South Kordofan Conflict</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/UNSC%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>Visegrad 4 Committee</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Chair: Sabine Hoferov&aacute;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Topic: A Common Energy Policy &amp; V4 Foreign Relations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Study Guide: <a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/V4%20-%20Study%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'committess_main'),
(20, '<p>\r\n	<b>MUN Rules</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Download the essential publication - &quot;BratMUN: The Complete Guide&quot; here:<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://bratmun.sk/doc/BratMUN%20-%20The%20Complete%20Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download (PDF)</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	This document is the perfect preparation material and is highly recommended to by read by all the delegates participating at the conference.<br />\r\n	The Guide includes:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-MUN Terms &amp; Phrases</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-Flow of the Debate Chart</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>-BratMUN Rules of Procedure</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-Summary of Points and Motions</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-Path to a Resolution Chart</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-Resolution Writing Guide</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-How to Write a Policy Statement</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-Conference Staff</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	-Structure of the Conference</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'preparation_mun_rules'),
(12, '<p>\r\n	<b>Conference Fees</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The conference fees had to be slightly changed, we apologize for this unexpected change.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>-With Accommodation</b> (Only for foreign delegates. Foreign delegates are strongly advised to apply for accomodation securing, since we are offering a hotel of good quality close to the city centre with a special discount for BratMUN delegates. There is the opportunity to elongate the accomodation in the hotel after the conference if desired.) <strong>Foreign delegates who are in financial need or have to travel great distances to Bratislava can apply for significant fee reduction by contacting the project managers!</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	80&euro;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	included: participation fee, hotel accommodation (3 nights), breakfast at the hotel, 3x lunch in a restaurant, banquet, all the equipment and support</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>-Slovak delegates with Accomodation </strong>(only for delegates of Slovak nationality who want to have their accomodation secured)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	65&euro;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	included: participation fee, hotel accomodation (3 nights), breakfast at the hotel,3x lunch in a restauarant,banquet,all the equipment and support</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>-Without Accommodation</b>&nbsp;(for Bratislava delegates and delegates securing accommodation of their own choice)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	35&euro;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	included: participation fee, 3x lunch in a restaurant, banquet, all the equipment and support</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	-<b>Teachers accompanying delegations do not pay any fees</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>PAYMENT INFORMATION</b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; line-height: 5.0px; font: 14.0px Arial; color: #2525dc">\r\n	<br />\r\n	<span style="color:#ffffff;"><b><span style="font-family:georgia,serif;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px