(41, 'British International School of Bratislava', 'Pekníkova 6 ', '00 421 2 6930 7081 (2)', 'Slovakia', 'Bratislava', 'no', 'Andy Pheby', '+421918364741', 'apheby@bisb.sk', 'Mina ', 'Cho', 'Oct.9.1995', 'Female', '+421910329957', 'mcho@bisb.sk', 'M44208836', 'DISEC', 'No', '', 'Jae Young', 'Yoo', '19/04/1996', 'Female', '+421907056915', 'joanneyoo96@yahoo.com', 'M84893292', 'UNSC', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Brazil, China, India', 'no', 'Do you find the revolution in Egypt to be succesfull after Hosni Mubarak has been thrown down? What are the biggest risks when a military council is running the country?', 'Yes, the revolution was successful because it threw down Mubarak, who was a corrupt pollitical leader who took advantage of the citizens and even attempted numerous assasinations. When a military council is\r\n running the country, they are likely to suppress the citizens'' opinions and rule the state by themselves. Also, any riots or uprisings that oppose the military government will be crushed by force, leading to the accumulation of oppositions. There are higher chances of revolutions, which will result in economical, social, and political instability. This later will have devastating effects on not only the country itself, but to the nations that are in relationship to it as well. A military council will also hamper the development of the nation by destroying the will of workers to work and contribute to the growth of the state''s economy. ', '', NULL),
(42, 'Gymnázium Poštová 9', 'Poštová 9', '00421556226604', 'Slovakia', 'Košice', 'no', '-', '-', '-', 'Peter', 'Béreš', '14.07.1993', 'Male', 'Peter', 'Béreš', 'EA057953', 'UNODC ', 'BratMun 2010, debating competitions in slovak language', '', 'Michal', 'Mazúr', '21.02.1994', 'Male', '0948 377 009', '0michal.m@gmail.com', 'EA603792', 'UNHRC ', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Mexico', 'yes', 'Are you able to find ideological differences between Facism and Nazism?', '     Facism and Nazism may seem very similar, but there are many differences between those two. First and probably the main difference is that Facism was developed in Italy by Benito Mussolini, name of this ideology was derived from revolutionary workers groups in Italy named "fasci revoluzionari". \r\n     \r\n    On the other hand, Nazism was founded in Germany by Adolf Hitler, original name of this ideology is "Nationalsozialismus" Second difference, however no less important, is that ideology of Nazism was based on nothing but racial hatred. Hitler believed that there is only one "master race" (Aryan race), and other races are supposed to serve for this race. For facists it was the state, which was the most important element, not the race as in Nazism. \r\n    Briefly said, if you accepted their language and their culture, they would leave you alone. Facists had NO strong opinions of any race, until in 1938 Hitler forced Mussolini to introduce believes of Nazism to Italian people ( these opinions were perceived as un-fascist or un-italian).\r\n\r\n    To summarize this, Facism was founded in Italy by B. Mussolini and the main element of it was the state. On the other hand, Nazism was founded in Germany by A. Hitler, and it was based on racial hatred.', '', NULL),
(43, 'Evangelical Lyceum', 'Vranovska 2', '0263838488', 'Slovakia', 'Bratislava  85102', 'no', 'Kathryn Fredell', '0915080391', 'Kathyfredell@yahoo.com', 'Marek ', 'Žaškovský', '27.12.1992', 'Male', '+421 918 444 426', 'Marek.Zaskovsky@gmail.com', 'EA013090', 'UNODC ', 'none', '', 'Filip', 'Fabian', '23.09.1994', 'Male', '0915648510', 'fabian.phill@gmail.com', 'EA716091', 'UNHRC ', 'None', '', 'Martin', 'Miklos', '21.06.1994', 'Male', '00421910215630', 'martinmiklos@gmail.com', 'EA648145', 'ECOFIN', 'None', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'UK, Russia, Japan, China, Germany, Columbia', 'no', 'Why are countries like Slovakia still not willing to recognize Kosovo?', 'Countries like Slovakia are unwilling to recognize Kosovo for three main reasons.\r\n\r\nFirst, the independence of Kosovo was declared without previous agreement of the UN, which was a violation of UN Resolution 1244 from the year 1999. In addition, the declaration of independence was a unilateral agreement without the Serbian government´s approval. \r\n \r\nSecond, recognition of Kosovo´s independence would be a violation of territorial integrity and the sovereignty of Serbia, which are the main principles of international law. Also, recognition of Kosovo may lead to destability and disruption of the fragile peace in the Balkan region.\r\n\r\nLast, the EU countries which rejected Kosovo as a sovereign state, such as Greece, Cyprus, Spain or Slovakia, have similar problems with ethnic minorities and separatist groups. Recognition of Kosovo could be a trigger for these groups to take action.   \r\n\r\nFor these reasons, it is difficult for countries like Slovakia to recognize the sovereignty of Kosovo.  \r\n', '', NULL),
(44, 'Súkromné gymnázium', 'Oravská cesta 11', '041/ 7235315 ', 'Slovakia', 'Žilina', 'no', 'Mgr. Gabriela Králiková', '+421914173112', 'kralikova@ssag.sk', 'Denisa', 'Gallová', '15.04.1993', 'Female', '+421902333372', 'nisse.gallova@hotmail.com', 'ST329894', 'UNSC', 'LEMUN 2010', '', 'Alexandra', 'Kolínová', '11.12.1994', 'Female', '+421908247304', 'kolinova94@gmail.com', 'EA985754', 'UNHRC ', 'none', '', 'Samuel', 'Milučký', '05.10.1993', 'Male', '+421908093766', 'samuel.milucky@gmail.com', 'EA263369', 'SPECPOL ', 'none', '', 'Paulína', 'Vráblová', '21.03.1994', 'Female', '+421911228409', 'vrablova.paulina@gmail.com', 'EB261712', 'ECOFIN', 'none', '', 'Lukáš', 'Mlynár', '06.04.1994', 'Male', '+421944531872', 'mlynar.lukas@gmail.com', 'EA530816', 'UNODC ', 'none', '', '1. USA, 2.United Kingdom, 3. France, 4.Germany', 'yes', 'Greece supports the turkeys membership in EU although these two countries have had numerous disputes over their territory, for example the Cyprus dispute, that still isnt fully resolved . What benefits would Greece have from Turkeys EU membership?', 'Despite of many disputes between Turkey and Greece there are numerous benefits for Greece in case of Turkey joining the EU. Our delegation has chosen to name some of them mostly connected with the trade. \r\nFirstly, opening the borders of Greece for Turkey would attract Turkish people to work there because of Greek social system benefits that is above the average in Europe, therefore Greece could take adventage of cheaper labour force from Turkey. \r\nSecondly, Turkey joining the EU and possible accepting of EURO currency would mean no more expenses in trading caused by high  exchange rate and paying custom duties. And also cheaper goods from Turkey could be available.  Especially in clothing production.\r\nAnother benefit would be security insurance in case of Cyprus dispute. These countries would be forced to maintain the status quo on border issues and another armed conflicts should be completely excluded and solved peacefully. \r\n', 'none', NULL),
(45, 'Evangelical Lyceum', 'Vranovska 2', '0263838488', 'Slovakia', 'Bratislava', 'no', 'Kathryn Fredell', '0915080391', 'Kathyfredell@yahoo.com', 'Lucia', 'Durajkova', '24.07.1992', 'Female', '0944330473', 'durajkova.lucia@gmail.com', 'EA176522', 'UNODC ', 'none', '', 'Veronika', 'Cervenakova', '7.04.1994', 'Female', '0911082085', 'Vercacerv@gmail.com', 'EA454969', 'UNODC ', 'none', '', 'Zuzana', 'Prostrednikova', '20.01.1994', 'Female', '0904519106', 'zprostrednikova@gmail.com', 'EA352984', 'UNHRC ', 'None', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Germany, France,UK, Russia, US', 'no', 'Are you able to find ideological differences between Facism and Nazism?', 'The differences between fascism and Nazism are in their roots and approach to people.  Different ruling systems in Italy and Germany produced two ideological leaders- Mussolini and Hitler. To protect their positions, these leaders used different approaches to the people.  Mussolini taught young people to be proud of their origin and created a better Italy that respected traditional social attitudes. Mussolini’s fascism focused on nationalism and preservation of culture.   Although Hitler also took care of young citizens, he focused on racism and creating a superior race.  The fascists were never as repressive or as savage as the Nazis.  The biggest difference between fascism and Nazism is that fascism wanted to preserve and promote nationalism and culture while Nazism wanted to create a superior race excluding all other people.', '', NULL),
(46, 'Bilingvalne Gymnazium CS Lewisa', 'Benadicka 38', '02/6382 6147', 'Slovakia', 'Bratislava', 'no', 'Gina Hochreiter', '0915 034 690', 'gina.hochreiter@bilgym.sk', 'Katarína ', 'Kondrótová', '1.12.1995', 'Female', '0908938190', 'katkakondrotova@gmail.com', 'EB427670', 'UNHRC ', 'none', '', 'Peter', 'Janiš', '07.03.1995', 'Male', '0910163072', 'ptrjanis@gmail.com', 'EB120083', 'ECOFIN', 'Slovak Debate League', '', 'Branislav', 'Jánošík', '20.11.1991', 'Male', '0915443596', 'bjanosik@gmail.com', 'EB193936', 'UNHRC ', 'none', '', 'Anna', 'Jávorková', '5.10.1992', 'Female', '0915443596', 'anna.javorka@hotmail.com', 'EB581649', 'UNODC ', 'none', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'any European or Middle Eastern country available', 'no', 'Do you find the revolution in Egypt to be succesfull after Hosni Mubarak has been thrown down? What are the biggest risks when a military council is running the country?', 'The main priority of Turkey in the contemporary world situation must be the improvement of relations with Europe (the EU). In order to perform this master target, three simple steps (fulfilling three simple goals) must be executed. At first, the Turkish army has to withdraw from Cyprus completely. It is obvious that if we want to become a part of the EU, Cyprus has to agree. Therefore, it is essential to perform the second step – return the Turkish part of Cyprus to its original owner. Naturally, several other reparations will have to take place if Cyprus is required to forget the affairs of past and accept Turkey into the European Union. At this point, after the relations with Cyprus will have been restored, step number three must be executed.  We will demand to be accepted into the EU and significantly improve our business and political relations towards our European neighbors.', 'I know we are close to the deadline, so we are willing to accept whatever committees are available. Peter and Katka would prefer a European country, and Anna and Brano would prefer a Middle Eastern country. However, I realize that this may not be possible', NULL),
(47, 'Secondary Grammar School of Michal Miloslav Hodža', 'Hodžova 860/9', '044/55 183 32', 'Slovakia', 'Liptovský Mikuláš', 'no', 'Mgr. Lýdia Čajková', '00421908459745', 'cajka.lydia@gmail.com', 'Natália ', 'Gmucová', '30.06.1993', 'Female', '00421910569108', 'gmucova.natalie@yahoo.com', 'EA009103', 'UNHRC ', 'TALEC', 'reg/registration_47/photos/delegate_1_photo(Natália ).jpg', 'Ivona', 'Harčarová', '09.10.1992', 'Female', '00421905205660', 'harcarova.i@gmail.com', 'SL835208', 'UNHRC ', 'TALEC', 'reg/registration_47/photos/delegate_2_photo(Ivona).jpg', 'Michal ', 'Kukučka', '22.11.1992', 'Male', '+421907513512', 'mikloko22@gmail.com', 'EA012092', 'ECOFIN', 'TALEC', 'reg/registration_47/photos/delegate_3_photo(Michal ).jpg', 'Juraj', 'Majerík', '19.04.1993', 'Male', '+421944222341', 'juro.majerik@gmail.com', 'EB097527', 'UNSC', 'TALEC', 'reg/registration_47/photos/delegate_4_photo(Juraj).jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'USA, Russia, China, United Kingdom', 'yes', 'You are an Iranian president delivering a speech at the UN. Talk briefly about the disadvantages of capitalism.', 'Let me begin by thanking for this opportunity to talk about this issue.\r\n\r\nI would like to talk briefly about main disadvantages we think capitalism has got.\r\n\r\nFirstly, it is inequality among people. Only a small percentage of population has got the access to wealth. Lots of people suffer from lack of essential needs for everyday life. Moreover, not all the people from various backrounds have chance to get a quality education and qualification.\r\n\r\nAnother disadvantage is that firms have gained monopoly power over free market in the country and that is why they tend to exploit their workers and also dictate price.\r\n\r\nFinally, it should be a duty of government to furnish all citizens with equal rights to provide them with work and to satisfy them with basic needs.\r\n\r\nWe are the right example of a country where branches of power cooperate effectively without any use of capitalism.', '', NULL),
(48, 'II Liceum Ogólnokształcące', 'Wróblewskiego 9', '+48322311213', 'Poland', 'Gliwice', 'no', 'Ewa Konieczna', '+48501828428', 'ewa.necessary@gmail.com', 'Marta', 'Chadalska', '20.09.1993', 'Female', '+48514679686', 'chadalska.marta@gmail.com', 'ATM717158', 'UNODC ', 'none', '', 'Ewelina', 'Marszowska', '7.03.1993', 'Female', '+48698079171', 'marszowska@interia.pl', 'ATM717158', 'SPECPOL ', 'none', '', 'Michał', 'Frąckowiak', '8.02.1994', 'Male', '+48501381345', 'frackowiak.michal@gmail.com', 'AL1074630', 'UNHRC ', 'none', '', 'Bartłomiej', 'Kordalski', '25.05.1994', 'Male', '501983713', 'b.kordalski@gmail.com', 'AT3914967', 'ECOFIN', 'none', '', 'Mateusz Cichy', 'cichacz7@gmail.com', '15.11.1994', 'Male', '+48695995558', 'cichacz7@gmail.com', 'AS0439329', 'SPECPOL ', 'none', '', 'Poland,  Czech Republic, Germany,  Austria,  Russian Fed. ', 'yes', 'Are you able to find ideological differences between Facism and Nazism?', 'Nazism and fascism are similar ideologies however we are able to pinpoint some differences.\r\nNazism is an advanced and more radical form of fascism. The most important difference is that\r\nnazists were more radical racists and antisemites than fascists. Fascists were looking for support\r\nfrom the church and nazists were inspired by folk tradition and they were anti-religious. Fascists\r\nwanted to conquer other countries in the name of aggressive imperialism and nazists in the name of\r\nrasism. Nazists thought thatn their nation was the best and most important and it was above other\r\nnations. Fascists created only the cult of their country.', '', NULL),
(49, 'Gymnázium Ľudovíta Štúra', 'Hronská 1467/3, Zvolen 960 49', '+421455332098', 'Slovakia', 'Zvolen', 'no', 'Mgr. Jana Hameršmídová', '+421455332098', 'jana.hamersmidova@gymzv.sk', 'Matúš', 'Žiga', '13/02/1993', 'Male', '+421907030166', 'matoziga@gmail.com', 'ST185983', 'SPECPOL ', 'Debate with Charge d''affaires Georges Lemieux, Debate with MEP Monika Flašíková-Beňová', 'reg/registration_49/photos/delegate_1_photo(Matúš).jpg', 'Pavol', 'Krajči', '24/09/1993', 'Male', '+421907409793', 'krajci.pavol@gmail.com', 'EA196364­', 'SPECPOL ', 'Debate with Charge d''affaires Georges Lemieux', 'reg/registration_49/photos/delegate_2_photo(Pavol).jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Cyprus, Turkey, Greece, UK, Austria, Germany, Belgium', 'yes', 'Are you able to find ideological differences between Facism and Nazism?', 'Nazism is considered to be one form of fascism. Both Nazism and fascism reject the ideologies of liberalism, Marxism, and democracy. They have origin in the 20th century. Fascism was modish between 1919 and 1945, while Nazism was in vogue from 1933 to 1945. Fascism was originally referred to the Fascists in Italy, who were under the influence of Mussolini. On the other hand, Nazism is ideological concept of Adolf Hitler’s Nazi Party. Fascism believes in the corporatism of all elements in the society to form an Organic State. They emphasize on nationalism, corporatism, totalitarianism, and militarism. On the contrary, Nazism emphasize on racism. They believe in the superiority of the Aryan race. For Fascists, the state was the most important element while Nazism considered Aryanism as more important.', 'Krajči - vegetarian food', NULL),
(50, 'The English College in Prague', 'Sokolovska 320', '+420 283 893 113', 'Czech Republic', 'Prague', 'yes', 'Nicholas Hill', '+420 722 190 006', 'nicholas.hill@college.cz', 'Milan', 'Bednar', '5/2/1994', 'Male', '+420736453620', 'bednar6@gmail.com', '112702383', 'DISEC', 'BISMUN 2011', '', 'Lukas', 'Cejnar', '15/8/1994', 'Male', '+420 737 954 3664', 'lukas.cejnar@gmail.com', '113 248 574', 'DISEC', 'BISMUN 2011', '', 'Veronika', 'Havlova', '17/10/1994', 'Female', '+420 722 091 925', 'veru_fido@hotmail.com', '113676564', 'DISEC', 'BISMUN 2011', '', 'Veronika', 'Vohlmuthova', '17/8/21994', 'Female', '+420 777 602 381', 'verunkaXD@seznam.cz', '115335846', 'ECOFIN', '-', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Czech Republic', 'no', 'Are you able to find ideological differences between Facism and Nazism?', 'Nazism is not so much a political ideology as Fascism. It is merely a very regimented and extreme version of Fascism and is mostly associated with the political party in Germany. On the other hand, Fascism is an ideology that can occur in many countries.', 'Lukas Cejnar, Milan Bednar and Veronika Havlova are applying for V4.', NULL),
